      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.223-9</ph> Estimate of Percentage of Recovered Material Content for EPA-Designated Items.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="clause" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e8">As prescribed in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref base="i1094741"
                     href="23.109.dita#FAR_23_109"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">23.109</xref>(b)(2)</ph>, insert the following clause:</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e15" outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps">Estimate of Percentage of Recovered Material Content for EPA-Designated Items <ph outputclass="SmCaps" class="- topic/ph ">(May 2008)</ph>
         </p>
         <ol id="d3341e25" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e21">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Definitions</i>. As used in this clause-</p>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e27">
                  <i outputclass="Term"
                     xtrf="_52.223-9"
                     xtrc="d3376e40"
                     class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Postconsumer material</i>means a material or finished product that has served its intended use and has been discarded for disposal or recovery, having completed its life as a consumer item. Postconsumer material is a part of the broader category of "recovered material."</p>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e31">"Recovered material" means waste materials and by-products recovered or diverted from solid waste, but the term does not include those materials and by-products generated from, and commonly reused within, an original manufacturing process.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e34">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
						            The Contractor, on completion of this contract, shall-</p>
               <ol id="d3341e56" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e40">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                Estimate the percentage of the total recovered material content for EPA-designated item(s) delivered and/or used in contract performance, including, if applicable, the percentage of post-consumer material content; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3380e45">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>  Submit this estimate to <cite outputclass="MultiLine"
                              xtrc="52.223-9_d3365e70"
                              xtrf="GFI"
                              class="- topic/cite ">_____________________ [<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contracting Officer complete in accordance with agency procedures</i>]</cite>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
         <section outputclass="Alternate" class="- topic/section "><?FM MARKER [Alt] Start?>
            <p class="- topic/p " id="d3383e57">
               <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Alternate I </i>
               <ph outputclass="SmCaps" class="- topic/ph ">(May 2008)</ph>. As prescribed in<ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                  <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref base="i1094741"
                           href="23.109.dita#FAR_23_109"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">23.109</xref>(b)(2)</ph>, </ph>redesignate paragraph (b) of the basic clause as paragraph (c) and add the following paragraph (b) to the basic clause:</p>
            <p outputclass="List1" class="- topic/p ">(b) The Contractor shall execute the following certification required by the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act of 1976 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section6962(i)(2)(C)&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html"
                     class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. 6962(i)(2)(C)</xref>):</p>
            <p outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" class="- topic/p ">Certification</p>
            <p outputclass="NoIndent" class="- topic/p ">I, <cite outputclass="SingleLine"
                     xtrc="52.223-9_d1e120"
                     xtrf="VFI"
                     class="- topic/cite ">_______________ (name of certifier)</cite>, am an officer or employee responsible for the performance of this contract and hereby certify that the percentage of recovered material content for EPA-designated items met the applicable contract specifications or other contractual requirements.</p>
